            <notesStmt>
                <note type="summary">
                    
                        
                            <p>This is a letter from Edward O&#39;Farrell (1857-1926) to James Jackson Clark (1846-1926), a Colonel from Derry. This letter is a reply to a letter sent by Clark requesting a pass to travel to England. In this letter O&#39;Farrell states that the Lord Lieutenant, Ivor Guest (1873-1939) has informed him that there are no passes being permitted, and that Clark should apply for a certificate from his Local District Inspector to satisfy the Military Authorities. </p>
                        
                    
                </note>
